void DBus::init ( bool  threadsafe = true)

Initializes the dbus-cxx library.

Parameters
threadsafeIf true the library's threadsafe structures, along with the underlying dbus library will be initialized to support threadsafe operations. This makes the library threadsafe at the cost of efficiency.
Examples:
calculator_client.cpp, calculator_server.cpp, calculator_watcher.cpp, callee.cpp, callee_2.cpp, callee_dispatched.cpp, callee_object.cpp, callee_object_inherited.cpp, callee_raw.cpp, caller_dispatched.cpp, caller_object.cpp, caller_raw.cpp, signal_emitter.cpp, signal_emitter_2.cpp, signal_emitter_3.cpp, signal_emitter_object.cpp, signal_emitter_raw.cpp, signal_receiver.cpp, signal_receiver_2.cpp, signal_receiver_object.cpp, and signal_receiver_raw.cpp.
